    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the multiverse thing doesn't feel right. it felt too... efficient. like, it wasn't a parallel world, it was just the same asset being reused. like a glitch in a game where the system can't keep track of every unique NPC so it just reloads one it already has in memory. if you think about it, the \"detail\" theory makes more sense. if i start looking for more of these \"reused\" things, do you think i could actually find the edge of where the rendering fails?",
